nds created sensitive wind drifts in areas with colder snow. Watch for wind-loaded slopes, especially on north through east aspects, and avoid steep terrain where snow is actively drifting.<\/p>"}]},"terrainAndTravelAdvice":{"days":[[],[],[]]},"communication":{"headline":"","sms":""},"media":{"Images":[{"id":"cd02320f-1315-4bae-9802-f86be9befffa","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1777925763\/AvIDfx\/y1zh94kj1tcsaiym53ba.webp","width":350,"height":263,"credit":"","caption":"<p>Avalanches like this will be easy to trigger on Friday and through the weekend. Avoid very steep slopes where the snow feels wet.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"Fresh snow avalanched from an alpine coulior","dateTaken":"2026-05-01T20:16:09.019Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"4bb9a955-3f28-4069-b1c5-1a9aa8276990","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1778189416\/AvIDfx\/sq8b9ryll4rqtqba4sy1.webp","width":350,"height":263,"credit":"","caption":"<p>On Wednesday an avalanche released in the Dragons Tail Couloir in RMNP carrying two skiers. Avalanches like this will possible from Friday through the weekend. Avoid stiff drifted slabs and wet snow in very steep terrain.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"avy","dateTaken":"2026-05-06T21:31:17.136Z","isArchived":false}]},"dangerRatings":{"days":[{"position":1,"alp":"moderate","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-05-08T22:30:00Z"},{"position":2,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-05-09T22:30:00Z"},{"position":3,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-05-10T22:30:00Z"}]},"avalancheProblems":{"days":[[{"type":"wetLoose","aspectElevations":["n_alp","ne_alp","e_alp","se_alp","s_alp","nw_alp"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}},{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","ne_alp","e_alp","se_alp"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[],[]]}},{"id":"f053176e-7405-4e03-bed2-7762da907574","publicName":"104-105-106-107-108-